        "subject": "LU-19211 utils: skip testing for non-functional patches",
        "message": "LU-19211 utils: skip testing for non-functional patches\n\nchanged.py is used by Autotest to analyze patches for additional\ntesting.  The current output of the script lists changed subtests\nand affected files.  For example:\n\n    {\n      \"updated_tests\": {\n        \"sanity-hsm\": [\"test_11d\"]\n      },\n      \"affected_files\": {\n        \"m\": [\"lustre/mdd/mdd_object.c\", \"lustre/tests/sanity-hsm.sh\"],\n        \"a\": [],\n        \"d\": []\n      }\n    }\n\nThere is also a skip_testing feature which tells Autotest to send\n+1 and not run any testing for patches with only non-functional\nchanges (i.e. Documentation/, contrib/, LICENSES/, etc.)\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Charlie Olmstead <charlie@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I9bd32b5f6ed9e1e2c346f21195f7e5c726ca2cf6\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60584\nReviewed-by: Timothy Day <timday@thelustrecollective.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
